# The Kaini/Bocuma voice, corrected architecture: an SH-101 is ONE
# VCO whose saw and sub are phase-locked outputs of the same core.
# Faking the mixer with separate free-running oscillators makes a
# thin beating double — so this patch uses only osc1 (saw) plus the
# TRUE sub-oscillator, which is phase-locked to the core by
# construction (the divider shares its phase), exactly like the
# hardware. One solid voice.
# Filter: key-followed ladder with a breathing envelope; driven and
# saturated for body. Wow/reverb live in the song.
waveform 2
osc2_wave 2
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0
osc3_wave 2
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 0
sub 0.7
circuit 0
key_track 0.7
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0.03
pulse_width 0.5
attack 0.018
decay 1.0
sustain 0.6
release 0.5
filter_env 1.2
filter_attack 0.005
filter_decay 0.8
filter_sustain 0.55
filter_release 0.5
cutoff 1150
resonance 1.1
drive 1.7
saturation 0.8
hpf 16
